#. <section class="sutta" id="mn44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn44:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 44"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 44"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn44:0.2"
msgid "Cūḷavedallasutta"
msgstr "The Shorter Analysis"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.299"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "mn44:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "mn44:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "mn44:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho visākho upāsako yena dhammadinnā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho visākho upāsako dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the layman Visākha went to see the nun Dhammadinnā, bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to her:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:2.1"
msgid "“‘sakkāyo sakkāyo’ti, ayye, vuccati."
msgstr "“Ma’am, they speak of this thing called ‘identity’."

msgctxt "mn44:2.2"
msgid "Katamo nu kho, ayye, sakkāyo vutto bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "What is this identity that the Buddha spoke of?”"

msgctxt "mn44:2.3"
msgid "“Pañca kho ime, āvuso visākha, upādānakkhandhā sakkāyo vutto bhagavatā,"
msgstr ""
"“Visākha, the Buddha said that these five grasping aggregates are identity."

msgctxt "mn44:2.4"
msgid ""
"seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr "That is: form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "mn44:2.5"
msgid "Ime kho, āvuso visākha, pañcupādānakkhandhā sakkāyo vutto bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha said that these five grasping aggregates are identity.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:2.6"
msgid ""
"“Sādhayye”ti kho visākho upāsako dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā bhāsitaṃ "
"abhinanditvā anumoditvā dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ uttariṃ pañhaṃ apucchi:"
msgstr ""
"Saying “Good, ma’am,” Visākha approved and agreed with what Dhammadinnā "
"said. Then he asked another question:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:3.1"
msgid "“‘sakkāyasamudayo sakkāyasamudayo’ti, ayye, vuccati."
msgstr "“Ma’am, they speak of this thing called ‘the origin of identity’."

msgctxt "mn44:3.2"
msgid "Katamo nu kho, ayye, sakkāyasamudayo vutto bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "What is the origin of identity that the Buddha spoke of?”"

msgctxt "mn44:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Yāyaṃ, āvuso visākha, taṇhā ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā "
"tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and "
"greed, taking pleasure in various different realms. That is,"

msgctxt "mn44:3.4"
msgid "kāmataṇhā bhavataṇhā vibhavataṇhā;"
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to "
"end existence."

msgctxt "mn44:3.5"
msgid "ayaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyasamudayo vutto bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha said that this is the origin of identity.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:4.1"
msgid "“‘Sakkāyanirodho sakkāyanirodho’ti, ayye, vuccati."
msgstr "“Ma’am, they speak of this thing called ‘the cessation of identity’."

msgctxt "mn44:4.2"
msgid "Katamo nu kho, ayye, sakkāyanirodho vutto bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "What is the cessation of identity that the Buddha spoke of?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:4.3"
msgid ""
"“Yo kho, āvuso visākha, tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo "
"paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo;"
msgstr ""
"“It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing "
"left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not clinging to "
"it."

msgctxt "mn44:4.4"
msgid "ayaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyanirodho vutto bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha said that this is the cessation of identity.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:5.1"
msgid ""
"“‘Sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti, ayye, "
"vuccati."
msgstr ""
"“Ma’am, they speak of the practice that leads to the cessation of identity."

msgctxt "mn44:5.2"
msgid "Katamā nu kho, ayye, sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā vuttā bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What is the practice that leads to the cessation of identity that the Buddha "
"spoke of?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:5.3"
msgid ""
"“Ayameva kho, āvuso visākha, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sakkāyanirodhagāminī "
"paṭipadā vuttā bhagavatā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“The practice that leads to the cessation of identity that the Buddha spoke "
"of is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn44:5.4"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo "
"sammāsati sammāsamādhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.300"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: te → teva (bj)
msgctxt "mn44:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Taññeva nu kho, ayye, upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā udāhu aññatra "
"pañcahupādānakkhandhehi upādānan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, is that grasping the exact same thing as the five grasping "
"aggregates? Or is grasping one thing and the five grasping aggregates "
"another?”"

msgctxt "mn44:6.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso visākha, taññeva upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā, nāpi "
"aññatra pañcahupādānakkhandhehi upādānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“That grasping is not the exact same thing as the five grasping aggregates. "
"Nor is grasping one thing and the five grasping aggregates another."

msgctxt "mn44:6.3"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, āvuso visākha, pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgo taṃ tattha "
"upādānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"The desire and greed for the five grasping aggregates is the grasping there.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:7.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ panāyye, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But ma’am, how does identity view come about?”"

msgctxt "mn44:7.2"
msgid ""
"“Idhāvuso visākha, assutavā puthujjano, ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa "
"akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa "
"akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto, "
msgstr ""
"“It’s when an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is "
"neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not "
"seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of "
"the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn44:7.3"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ "
"vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form."

msgctxt "mn44:7.4"
msgid "Vedanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They regard feeling …"

msgctxt "mn44:7.5"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn44:7.6"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn44:7.7"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, attani vā viññāṇaṃ, "
"viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "mn44:7.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how identity view comes about.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:8.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ panāyye, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But ma’am, how does identity view not come about?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:8.2"
msgid ""
"“Idhāvuso visākha, sutavā ariyasāvako, ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa "
"kovido ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido "
"sappurisadhamme suvinīto, "
msgstr ""
"“It’s when an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is "
"skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good "
"persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn44:8.3"
msgid ""
"na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā rūpaṃ, "
"na rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self "
"in form."

msgctxt "mn44:8.4"
msgid "Na vedanaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They don’t regard feeling …"

msgctxt "mn44:8.5"
msgid "na saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn44:8.6"
msgid "na saṅkhāre … pe …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn44:8.7"
msgid ""
"na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ, na attani vā "
"viññāṇaṃ, na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "mn44:8.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how identity view does not come about.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:9.1"
msgid "“Katamo panāyye, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo”ti?"
msgstr "“But ma’am, what is the noble eightfold path?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:9.2"
msgid "“Ayameva kho, āvuso visākha, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "mn44:9.3"
msgid ""
"sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo "
"sammāsati sammāsamādhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:10.1"
msgid "“Ariyo panāyye, aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhato udāhu asaṅkhato”ti?"
msgstr "“But ma’am, is the noble eightfold path conditioned or unconditioned?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.301"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:10.2"
msgid "“Ariyo kho, āvuso visākha, aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhato”ti."
msgstr "“The noble eightfold path is conditioned.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:11.1"
msgid ""
"“Ariyena nu kho, ayye, aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena tayo khandhā saṅgahitā udāhu "
"tīhi khandhehi ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅgahito”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Are the three practice categories included in the noble eightfold path? Or "
"is the noble eightfold path included in the three practice categories?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:11.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso visākha, ariyena aṭṭhaṅgikena maggena tayo khandhā saṅgahitā; "
"tīhi ca kho, āvuso visākha, khandhehi ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅgahito."
msgstr ""
"“The three practice categories are not included in the noble eightfold path. "
"Rather, the noble eightfold path is included in the three practice "
"categories."

msgctxt "mn44:11.3"
msgid ""
"Yā cāvuso visākha, sammāvācā yo ca sammākammanto yo ca sammāājīvo ime dhammā "
"sīlakkhandhe saṅgahitā."
msgstr ""
"Right speech, right action, and right livelihood: these things are included "
"in the category of ethics."

msgctxt "mn44:11.4"
msgid ""
"Yo ca sammāvāyāmo yā ca sammāsati yo ca sammāsamādhi ime dhammā "
"samādhikkhandhe saṅgahitā."
msgstr ""
"Right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion: these things are "
"included in the category of immersion."

msgctxt "mn44:11.5"
msgid ""
"Yā ca sammādiṭṭhi yo ca sammāsaṅkappo, ime dhammā paññākkhandhe saṅgahitā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Right view and right thought: these things are included in the category of "
"wisdom.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo panāyye, samādhi, katame dhammā samādhinimittā, katame dhammā "
"samādhiparikkhārā, katamā samādhibhāvanā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, what is immersion? What things are the basis of immersion? What "
"things are the prerequisites for immersion? What is the development of "
"immersion?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:12.2"
msgid "“Yā kho, āvuso visākha, cittassa ekaggatā ayaṃ samādhi;"
msgstr "“Unification of the mind is immersion."

msgctxt "mn44:12.3"
msgid "cattāro satipaṭṭhānā samādhinimittā;"
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the basis of immersion."

msgctxt "mn44:12.4"
msgid "cattāro sammappadhānā samādhiparikkhārā."
msgstr "The four right efforts are the prerequisites for immersion."

msgctxt "mn44:12.5"
msgid ""
"Yā tesaṃyeva dhammānaṃ āsevanā bhāvanā bahulīkammaṃ, ayaṃ ettha "
"samādhibhāvanā”ti."
msgstr ""
"The cultivation, development, and making much of these very same things is "
"the development of immersion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:13.1"
msgid "“Kati panāyye, saṅkhārā”ti?"
msgstr "“How many processes are there?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:13.2"
msgid "“Tayome, āvuso visākha, saṅkhārā—"
msgstr "“There are these three processes."

msgctxt "mn44:13.3"
msgid "kāyasaṅkhāro, vacīsaṅkhāro, cittasaṅkhāro”ti."
msgstr "Physical, verbal, and mental processes.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:14.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo panāyye, kāyasaṅkhāro, katamo vacīsaṅkhāro, katamo cittasaṅkhāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, what is the physical process? What’s the verbal process? What’s "
"the mental process?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:14.2"
msgid ""
"“Assāsapassāsā kho, āvuso visākha, kāyasaṅkhāro, vitakkavicārā vacīsaṅkhāro, "
"saññā ca vedanā ca cittasaṅkhāro”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Breathing is a physical process. Placing the mind and keeping it connected "
"are verbal processes. Perception and feeling are mental processes.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Kasmā panāyye, assāsapassāsā kāyasaṅkhāro, kasmā vitakkavicārā "
"vacīsaṅkhāro, kasmā saññā ca vedanā ca cittasaṅkhāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, why is breathing a physical process? Why are placing the mind "
"and keeping it connected verbal processes? Why are perception and feeling "
"mental processes?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:15.2"
msgid ""
"“Assāsapassāsā kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikā ete dhammā kāyappaṭibaddhā, tasmā "
"assāsapassāsā kāyasaṅkhāro."
msgstr ""
"“Breathing is physical. It’s tied up with the body, that’s why breathing is "
"a physical process."

msgctxt "mn44:15.3"
msgid ""
"Pubbe kho, āvuso visākha, vitakketvā vicāretvā pacchā vācaṃ bhindati, tasmā "
"vitakkavicārā vacīsaṅkhāro."
msgstr ""
"First you place the mind and keep it connected, then you break into speech. "
"That’s why placing the mind and keeping it connected are verbal processes."

msgctxt "mn44:15.4"
msgid ""
"Saññā ca vedanā ca cetasikā ete dhammā cittappaṭibaddhā, tasmā saññā ca "
"vedanā ca cittasaṅkhāro”ti."
msgstr ""
"Perception and feeling are mental. They’re tied up with the mind, that’s why "
"perception and feeling are mental processes.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:16.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ panāyye, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpatti hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, how does someone attain the cessation of perception and feeling?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:16.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso visākha, saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjantassa bhikkhuno evaṃ "
"hoti:"
msgstr "“A mendicant who is entering such an attainment does not think:"

msgctxt "mn44:16.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjissan’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajjāmī’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno’ti vā."
msgstr ""
"‘I will enter the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I am entering the "
"cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I have entered the cessation of "
"perception and feeling.’"

msgctxt "mn44:16.4"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāssa pubbeva tathā cittaṃ bhāvitaṃ hoti yaṃ taṃ tathattāya "
"upanetī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, their mind has been previously developed so as to lead to such a "
"state.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.302"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:17.1"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjantassa panāyye, bhikkhuno katame dhammā "
"paṭhamaṃ nirujjhanti—yadi vā kāyasaṅkhāro, yadi vā vacīsaṅkhāro, yadi vā "
"cittasaṅkhāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, which cease first for a mendicant who is entering the cessation "
"of perception and feeling: physical, verbal, or mental processes?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:17.2"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpajjantassa kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuno "
"paṭhamaṃ nirujjhati vacīsaṅkhāro, tato kāyasaṅkhāro, tato cittasaṅkhāro”ti."
msgstr "“Verbal processes cease first, then physical, then mental.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:18.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ panāyye, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhānaṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, how does someone emerge from the cessation of perception and "
"feeling?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:18.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso visākha, saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahantassa "
"bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“A mendicant who is emerging from such an attainment does not think:"

msgctxt "mn44:18.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahissan’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ "
"saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahāmī’ti vā, ‘ahaṃ "
"saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhito’ti vā."
msgstr ""
"‘I will emerge from the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I am "
"emerging from the cessation of perception and feeling’ or ‘I have emerged "
"from the cessation of perception and feeling.’"

msgctxt "mn44:18.4"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāssa pubbeva tathā cittaṃ bhāvitaṃ hoti yaṃ taṃ tathattāya "
"upanetī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, their mind has been previously developed so as to lead to such a "
"state.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:19.1"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahantassa panāyye, bhikkhuno katame "
"dhammā paṭhamaṃ uppajjanti—yadi vā kāyasaṅkhāro, yadi vā vacīsaṅkhāro, yadi "
"vā cittasaṅkhāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, which arise first for a mendicant who is emerging from the "
"cessation of perception and feeling: physical, verbal, or mental processes?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:19.2"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahantassa kho, āvuso visākha, "
"bhikkhuno paṭhamaṃ uppajjati cittasaṅkhāro, tato kāyasaṅkhāro, tato "
"vacīsaṅkhāro”ti."
msgstr "“Mental processes arise first, then physical, then verbal.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitaṃ panāyye, bhikkhuṃ kati phassā "
"phusantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, when a mendicant has emerged from the attainment of the "
"cessation of perception and feeling, how many kinds of contact do they "
"experience?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:20.2"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuṃ tayo "
"phassā phusanti—suññato phasso, animitto phasso, appaṇihito phasso”ti."
msgstr ""
"“They experience three kinds of contact: emptiness, signless, and undirected "
"contacts.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:21.1"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitassa panāyye, bhikkhuno kiṃninnaṃ "
"cittaṃ hoti kiṃpoṇaṃ kiṃpabbhāran”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But ma’am, when a mendicant has emerged from the attainment of the "
"cessation of perception and feeling, what does their mind slant, slope, and "
"incline to?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:21.2"
msgid ""
"“Saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhitassa kho, āvuso visākha, bhikkhuno "
"vivekaninnaṃ cittaṃ hoti, vivekapoṇaṃ vivekapabbhāran”ti."
msgstr "“Their mind slants, slopes, and inclines to seclusion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:22.1"
msgid "“Kati panāyye, vedanā”ti?"
msgstr "“But ma’am, how many feelings are there?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:22.2"
msgid "“Tisso kho imā, āvuso visākha, vedanā—"
msgstr "“There are three feelings:"

msgctxt "mn44:22.3"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā”ti."
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral feeling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:23.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamā panāyye, sukhā vedanā, katamā dukkhā vedanā, katamā adukkhamasukhā "
"vedanā”ti?"
msgstr "“What are these three feelings?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.303"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:23.2"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā sukhaṃ sātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr "“Anything felt physically or mentally as pleasant or enjoyable."

msgctxt "mn44:23.3"
msgid "ayaṃ sukhā vedanā."
msgstr "This is pleasant feeling."

msgctxt "mn44:23.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā dukkhaṃ asātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr "Anything felt physically or mentally as painful or unpleasant."

msgctxt "mn44:23.5"
msgid "ayaṃ dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr "This is painful feeling."

msgctxt "mn44:23.6"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, āvuso visākha, kāyikaṃ vā cetasikaṃ vā neva sātaṃ nāsātaṃ vedayitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Anything felt physically or mentally as neither pleasurable nor painful."

msgctxt "mn44:23.7"
msgid "ayaṃ adukkhamasukhā vedanā”ti."
msgstr "This is neutral feeling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:24.1"
msgid ""
"“Sukhā panāyye, vedanā kiṃsukhā kiṃdukkhā, dukkhā vedanā kiṃsukhā kiṃdukkhā, "
"adukkhamasukhā vedanā kiṃsukhā kiṃdukkhā”ti?"
msgstr "“What is pleasant and what is painful in each of the three feelings?”"

# “Change” doesn’t really work for viparinama here. I’m eating a yoghurt—yum! Someone gives me an ice-cream—yummier! Same for below; changing from one form of torture to another is not pleasant. Viparinama usually means “perish”, and so it must be here.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:24.2"
msgid "“Sukhā kho, āvuso visākha, vedanā ṭhitisukhā vipariṇāmadukkhā;"
msgstr ""
"“Pleasant feeling is pleasant when it remains and painful when it perishes."

msgctxt "mn44:24.3"
msgid "dukkhā vedanā ṭhitidukkhā vipariṇāmasukhā;"
msgstr ""
"Painful feeling is painful when it remains and pleasant when it perishes."

msgctxt "mn44:24.4"
msgid "adukkhamasukhā vedanā ñāṇasukhā aññāṇadukkhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Neutral feeling is pleasant when there is knowledge, and painful when there "
"is ignorance.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:25.1"
msgid ""
"“Sukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ anusayo anuseti, dukkhāya vedanāya kiṃ "
"anusayo anuseti, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya kiṃ anusayo anusetī”ti?"
msgstr "“What underlying tendencies underlie each of the three feelings?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:25.2"
msgid ""
"“Sukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya rāgānusayo anuseti, dukkhāya vedanāya "
"paṭighānusayo anuseti, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo anusetī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The underlying tendency for greed underlies pleasant feeling. The "
"underlying tendency for repulsion underlies painful feeling. The underlying "
"tendency for ignorance underlies neutral feeling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:26.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbāya nu kho, ayye, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo anuseti, sabbāya dukkhāya "
"vedanāya paṭighānusayo anuseti, sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya "
"avijjānusayo anusetī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do these underlying tendencies always underlie these feelings?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:26.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso visākha, sabbāya sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo anuseti, na "
"sabbāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo anuseti, na sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya "
"vedanāya avijjānusayo anusetī”ti."
msgstr "“No, they do not.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:27.1"
msgid ""
"“Sukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ pahātabbaṃ, dukkhāya vedanāya kiṃ pahātabbaṃ, "
"adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya kiṃ pahātabban”ti?"
msgstr "“What should be given up in regard to each of these three feelings?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:27.2"
msgid ""
"“Sukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya rāgānusayo pahātabbo, dukkhāya "
"vedanāya paṭighānusayo pahātabbo, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo "
"pahātabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The underlying tendency to greed should be given up when it comes to "
"pleasant feeling. The underlying tendency to repulsion should be given up "
"when it comes to painful feeling. The underlying tendency to ignorance "
"should be given up when it comes to neutral feeling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:28.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbāya nu kho, ayye, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo pahātabbo, sabbāya "
"dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo pahātabbo, sabbāya adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya "
"avijjānusayo pahātabbo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Should these underlying tendencies be given up regarding all instances of "
"these feelings?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.304"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:28.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, āvuso visākha, sabbāya sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo pahātabbo, na "
"sabbāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo pahātabbo, na sabbāya "
"adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo pahātabbo."
msgstr "“No, not in all instances."

msgctxt "mn44:28.3"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso visākha, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "mn44:28.4"
msgid "Rāgaṃ tena pajahati, na tattha rāgānusayo anuseti."
msgstr ""
"With this they give up greed, and the underlying tendency to greed does not "
"lie within that."

msgctxt "mn44:28.5"
msgid "Idhāvuso visākha, bhikkhu iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "And take a mendicant who reflects:"

msgctxt "mn44:28.6"
msgid ""
"‘kudāssu nāmāhaṃ tadāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharissāmi yadariyā etarahi "
"āyatanaṃ upasampajja viharantī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, when will I enter and remain in the same dimension that the noble ones "
"enter and remain in today?’"

msgctxt "mn44:28.7"
msgid ""
"Iti anuttaresu vimokkhesu pihaṃ upaṭṭhāpayato uppajjati pihāppaccayā "
"domanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Nursing such a longing for the supreme liberations gives rise to sadness due "
"to longing."

msgctxt "mn44:28.8"
msgid "Paṭighaṃ tena pajahati, na tattha paṭighānusayo anuseti."
msgstr ""
"With this they give up repulsion, and the underlying tendency to repulsion "
"does not lie within that."

msgctxt "mn44:28.9"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso visākha, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā, dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former "
"happiness and sadness, enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "mn44:28.10"
msgid "Avijjaṃ tena pajahati, na tattha avijjānusayo anusetī”ti."
msgstr ""
"With this they give up ignorance, and the underlying tendency to ignorance "
"does not lie within that.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.1"
msgid "“Sukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“But ma’am, what is the counterpart of pleasant feeling?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.2"
msgid "“Sukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya dukkhā vedanā paṭibhāgo”ti."
msgstr "“Painful feeling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc53"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.3"
msgid "“Dukkhāya pannāyye, vedanāya kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“What is the counterpart of painful feeling?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc54"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.4"
msgid "“Dukkhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya sukhā vedanā paṭibhāgo”ti."
msgstr "“Pleasant feeling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc55"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.5"
msgid "“Adukkhamasukhāya panāyye, vedanāya kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“What is the counterpart of neutral feeling?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc56"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.6"
msgid "“Adukkhamasukhāya kho, āvuso visākha, vedanāya avijjā paṭibhāgo”ti."
msgstr "“Ignorance.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc57"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.7"
msgid "“Avijjāya panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“What is the counterpart of ignorance?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc58"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.8"
msgid "“Avijjāya kho, āvuso visākha, vijjā paṭibhāgo”ti."
msgstr "“Knowledge.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc59"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.9"
msgid "“Vijjāya panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“What is the counterpart of knowledge?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc60"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.10"
msgid "“Vijjāya kho, āvuso visākha, vimutti paṭibhāgo”ti."
msgstr "“Freedom.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc61"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.11"
msgid "“Vimuttiyā panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“What is the counterpart of freedom?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc62"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.12"
msgid "“Vimuttiyā kho, āvuso visākha, nibbānaṃ paṭibhāgo”ti."
msgstr "“Extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc63"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:29.13"
msgid "“Nibbānassa panāyye, kiṃ paṭibhāgo”ti?"
msgstr "“What is the counterpart of extinguishment?”"

#. VAR: Accayāsi, āvuso → accasarāvuso (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn44:29.14"
msgid "“Accayāsi, āvuso visākha, pañhaṃ, nāsakkhi pañhānaṃ pariyantaṃ gahetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Your question goes too far, Visākha. You couldn’t figure out the limit of "
"questions."

msgctxt "mn44:29.15"
msgid ""
"Nibbānogadhañhi, āvuso visākha, brahmacariyaṃ, nibbānaparāyanaṃ "
"nibbānapariyosānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"For extinguishment is the culmination, destination, and end of the spiritual "
"life."

msgctxt "mn44:29.16"
msgid ""
"Ākaṅkhamāno ca tvaṃ, āvuso visākha, bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ "
"puccheyyāsi, yathā ca te bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsī”ti."
msgstr ""
"If you wish, go to the Buddha and ask him this question. You should remember "
"it in line with his answer.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.305"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc64"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:30.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho visākho upāsako dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā dhammadinnaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā "
"yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"And then the layman Visākha approved and agreed with what the nun "
"Dhammadinnā said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled "
"her, keeping her on his right. Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat "
"down to one side,"

msgctxt "mn44:30.2"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho visākho upāsako yāvatako ahosi dhammadinnāya "
"bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed."

msgctxt "mn44:30.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā visākhaṃ upāsakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "mn44:30.4"
msgid ""
"“paṇḍitā, visākha, dhammadinnā bhikkhunī, mahāpaññā, visākha, dhammadinnā "
"bhikkhunī."
msgstr "“The nun Dhammadinnā is astute, Visākha, she has great wisdom."

msgctxt "mn44:30.5"
msgid ""
"Mañcepi tvaṃ, visākha, etamatthaṃ puccheyyāsi, ahampi taṃ evamevaṃ "
"byākareyyaṃ, yathā taṃ dhammadinnāya bhikkhuniyā byākataṃ."
msgstr ""
"If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the "
"same way as the nun Dhammadinnā."

#. VAR: cevetassa → esovetassa (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: Evañca naṃ → evametaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn44:30.6"
msgid "Eso cevetassa attho. Evañca naṃ dhārehī”ti."
msgstr "That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc65"></a>
msgctxt "mn44:30.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn44:30.8"
msgid "Attamano visākho upāsako bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the layman Visākha was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn44:30.9"
msgid "Cūḷavedallasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
